Reasoning: The paper deals with interference alignment techniques in wireless communication networks, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the feasibility of perfect interference alignment within limited channel extensions, which could be considered as a signal processing problem falling under the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method to achieve perfect interference alignment based on the obtained conditions on the channel structure, which could be considered as a computational engineering problem falling under the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the necessary and sufficient conditions on the channel structure of a fully connected interference network with time-varying fading, which could be considered as a multimedia problem falling under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
